Cat | Solana Foundation, [14 Jan 2026 at 12:34:18]:
...Chat directly to the team here!


Jorrit - Light Protocol, [14 Jan 2026 at 14:14:54 (15 Jan 2026 at 00:19:22)]:
This is Zk id example I presented in the workshop
https://github.com/Lightprotocol/program-examples/tree/main/zk/zk-id

The zk id example uses Light Protocol to:

1. Compressed Addresses to create cheap nullifiers
2. store zk id credentials in existing Merkle trees indexed by Solana Rpcs
- you can use cheap nullifiers without 2 and vice versa


Cat | Solana Foundation, [14 Jan 2026 at 14:23:56]:
can we create our own arbitrary merkle tree and do inclusion proofs?


Jorrit - Light Protocol, [14 Jan 2026 at 15:27:02]:
you can create new zk compression State Merkle trees but it doesn't yield an advantage over using initialized ones.

For non zk compression sparse Merkle trees I would just create them directly in my program.

This is a sparse Merkle tree library that works with Solana Poseidon syscalls https://docs.rs/light-sparse-merkle-tree


