Jorrit - Light Protocol, [21 Jan 2026 at 12:40:45]:
Hey, light protocol doesnâ€™t natively support shielded transfers. It is infrastructure that makes it easier to build zk protocols on Solana such as shielded transfers.

You can use it to:
1. store your nullifiers without paying for rent exemption
2. Store utxo hashes in a Merkle tree without the need to run an indexer or create the Merkle tree accounts
3. both 1 & 2 work independently or together


